The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | GROUND REALITIES
                                                   GROUND REALITIES
                      
	The VCA Stadium at Jamtha in Nagpur will become the 40th ground in India and the 174th worldwide to host an ODI match. Nagpur will also become the 9th Indian city to have the distinction of hosting ODIs at two separate grounds.         
	The list:         
	 New Delhi (The Kotla, from 15/9/1982) and (Jawaharlal Nehru Stadium from 28/9/1984)         
	 Ahmedabad (Sardar Vallabhai Patel Stadium, Navarangpura, from 25/11/1981) and (Sardar Patel Gujarat Stadium, Motera from 5/10/1984)         
	 Mumbai (Wankhede, from 17/1/1987) and (Brabourne, from 23/10/1989)         
	 Chandigarh (Sector 16 Stadium, from 27/1/1985) and (PCA Stadium, Mohali, from 22/11/1993)         
	 Baroda (Moti Bagh Stadium, from 9/11/1983) and (IPCL/Reliance Stadium, from 28/10/1994)         
	 Visakhapatnam (Indira Priyadarshini Stadium, from 10/12/1988) and (ACA-VDCA Stadium, from 5/4/2005)         
	 Hyderabad (LB Shastri Stadium, from 10/9/1983) and (Rajiv Gandhi Stadium, from 16/11/2005)         
	 Indore (Nehru Stadium from 1/12/1983) and (Usharaje Trust Cricket Stadium, from 15/4/2006)         
	 Nagpur (Vidarbha CA Ground, Civil Lines, from 23/1/1985) and (VCA Stadium, Jamtha, from 28/10/2009)           COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                   
